<h3 class="ongoing"><a name="Schedule">Course Schedule</a></h3>

<div class="section">
The class follows the textbook rather closely.  Exact timing varies
  from year to year depending on student interest, weather, etc.
  <ul class="schedule">
    <li><b>Chapter 1:</b> Energy in Thermal Physics (2 weeks)
       <p>Portions of this chapter will be saved for later</p>
    <li><b>Chapter 2:</b> The Second Law (3 weeks)
    <li class="exam"><b>Exam 1</b> will cover Chapters 1 and 2
    <li><b>Chapter 3:</b> Interactions and Implications (3 weeks)
    <li><b>Chapter 5:</b> Free Energy and Chemical Thermodynamics (2 weeks)
    <p>We only cover sections 1-3</p>
    <li class="exam"><b>Exam 2</b> will cover Chapters 3, 5, and possibly parts of 6
    <li><b>Chapter 6:</b> Boltzmann Statistics (2 weeks)
    <li><b>Chapter 7:</b> Quantum Statistics (2 weeks)
    <p>We will cover sections 1-2, and bits of the rest as time allows</p>
    <li><b>Chapter 4:</b> Engines and Refrigerators (1 week)
    <p>We will only cover sections 1 and 2, to end the
    semester on a more practical note.</p>
          
         
          
</div>
